item.title: [+1290] Monsanto Caused an Estimated 150,000 Farmer Suicides
item.description: Monsanto-created debts caused 150,000 farmer suicides in India. Annual licensing fees required each year for GM seeds patented by Monsanto keep farmers impoverished. One bad yield due to drought or other reasons, plunges farmers so deep into debt that they resort to suicide.
